		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.edrants.com/samira-kawash-the-bat-segundo-show-522/" rel="bookmark">Samira Kawash (The Bat Segundo Show #522)</a></h1>
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
<div class="entry-meta">
			<div class="entry-excerpt">
			<p>This is the second of two shows devoted to Halloween. Did you know that there was once a chocolate bar called the Chicken Dinner?  That cigarette companies once considered candy to be a threat to discretionary spending?  Or that candy was used by the military for safety purposes?  We didn&#8217;t either, until we read Samira Kawash&#8217;s <i>Candy: A Century of Panic and Pleasure</I>. We discuss the serpentine history of candy with the Candy Professor herself!<br />
